div.p:
Many copies, of diuerse sorts haue been scattered, and sent abroad, some partiall, some vntrue, some slanderous; what is here set downe, for the truth thereof, shall be iustified: the onelie wrong, therein, is to his excellent Maiestie, a syllable of whose admirable speeches, it was pitty to loose, his wordes as they were vttered by him, being as Salomon speaketh, Like Apples of
               Pro. 25. 11 
               gold, vvith pictures of siluer; and therefore, I request thee good Reader, when thou commest to any of his Highnes speeches, to turne Martial his Apostrophe vpon me;
